texts.html: Move your mouse around a bit. The standard Google Maps directional arrows should pop up, with one little addition: a pair of double arrows. Click those. (Note: If youre enrolled in the new Google Maps UI beta, the arrows might not appear. Instead, hit the up arrow on your keyboard. Thanks for the heads up on this trick, Eric! If its still not working for you, see the note at the bottom of this post.)

texts.html: I figured itd just be a single, static shot, but no:  you can click all around the control room, complete with StreetViews signature panoramas, navigating all the way down below the main platform for a glimpse at the heart of the TARDIS itself. You dont seem to be able to click into any of the hallways   thats probably for the better, really, as we dont want any of you getting lost.

text: I'm with AndrewPincock. The show is pretty atrocious. But, a lot of people consider my interests to be awful, so no one is really truly correct in this situation.

texts.html: But one thing that I will not back down from is my opinion on the series' fan base. I have been to several comic conventions. As you know, those places are LOADED with weirdos and super fans alike. But the Who fans are by far the most obnoxious, most socially awkward and rude people I've ever met.
